metadata.name: Temporal #54
metadata.description:
"Temporal" is a generative (pure code) artwork of abstract colored geometric shapes and forms, mixed in a way that trying to simulate natural media

Technically, colored shapes and curves are drawn in a graphic buffer and my custom fragment shader process and transforms the buffer content into that noisy and scratched output. All are 100% code, no images used.

CONTROLS

KEYS:

- 1-4: Set resolution from 1x to 4x of the current dimension (possibly slower performance in higher values)
- S: Save a png file with the current resolution

- P: Change orientation to Portrait with aspect ratio 0.75 (useful eg. for printing)
- L: Change orientation to Landscape with ratio 4/3  (1.333..)
- O: Change orientation to Square (box)
  Due to some 1:1 ratio sensitive calculations, rendering output may differ when switching orientations

----
Made with p5js and custom shaders

metadata.name: GEOMORPHISM #29
metadata.description:
A 4444 character magic spell for my rayhatching framework to render thinking rocks.

This piece may take some time to render (about 1-3 minutes, depending on hardware). The rendering time is symbolic of the vastness and agelessness of these rock structures, it is recommended to use the rendering time to contemplate deeply the concept of time spans so incredibly long, that to experience them they would have to overwrite your memories several times and thus are impossible to truly comprehend.

To ponder how, if they are so old, how come some of them float? Are these rocks the fixtures and has time and space itself eroded around them?

This project uses an approach called "rejection sampling". This means the program generates a random set of parameters, and then checks/previews how the resulting image would look. It measures the amount of visible objects, light and shadows, and then determines whether these fall into acceptable ranges. If not, it generates a new set of parameters. For certain hashes over a 100 parameter sets may be checked before it accepts the image.

The features of this project are "cliff", "ground", "thing" and "sky". These are not parameters, they are actual measurements of the resulting image, indicating what percentage of the view is occupied.

This piece can be saved as an SVG and plotted. It is recommended to run a path order optimization tool such as vpype or axicli, this will greatly reduce plotting time.

Some options can be changed via the URL:

&w=.25 : The line width in millimetres.
&d=.4 : Line density (multiplier to linewidth).
&h=235 : Page height in millimetres. The aspect ratio is 16:9, for a width of 420mm, suitable for A3 plotting.

The line width is set to 0.25 millimetres to suit most common fine liner pen stroke widths when plotting. 

If you don't intend to plot this piece, perhaps also try rendering it at 0.2 or even 0.1 millimetres line width, for an even more detailed image (it will also take longer to render).

(c) 2022 by Piter Pasma

metadata.name: saprophyte #13
metadata.description:
saprophyte is a real-time interactive particle system based on the principles of stigmergy. 60,000  particles move around the canvas leaving trails behind them as they move, while each particle decides how to move based on the trails left by other particles around it. You can click to erase the trails in an area, forcing the particles to rebuild their structures anew.

Press "c" to capture an image. By default this will save an image at the resolution of the browser window. If you'd like to save an image at a different resolution, you can press "o" to override the browser's resolution and force the piece to render at a resolution of your choice, and then press "c" to capture the image at your chosen resolution. For best results, wait several seconds after changing the resolution to capture an image, as the piece may need time to adjust to the new resolution.

metadata.name: Versus #41
metadata.description:
"Versus" is a generative (pure code) decorative artwork of abstract and geometric shapes and forms, mixed in a way that trying to simulate natural material like chalk drawing or painting in a wall (eg. fresco) or cave that has been affected by corrosion and time passing. 

Is the art versus time, temporary ephemeral versus eternal, the evolution and continuous fighting against decay and absence.

Technically there are around 10 algorithmic stylers (traits and internals) that drawing shapes and curves in a graphic buffer according to some rules, and is a custom fragment shader I have developed which process and transforms the buffer content into that final output. 
All are 100% code, no images used.

CONTROLS

metadata.name: Football 2022 Memo #4
metadata.description:
INTRODUCTION
"Football 2022 Memo" is an Interactive flipping cards Memory Test Collectible, a Special Edition Memorabilia for the larger football - soccer even on the planet which took place in 2022 (once every 4 years). Consists of 3 different sections - pages. An introduction page - splash screen (with 3 random flags and the host Country - Qatar's flag), the game page and a short summary - real stats page.

DESCRIPTION
Created exclusively from scratch (except from the flag images) for this great football event which hosted in Qatar and can help you remember this "once per 4 years" world sports Event in two ways:
a) The game includes a short summary page with real stats
and b) You can keep your memory in good condition (or even improve it) by practicing in game page (no kidding)
Play alone or with another person in family or friend and if you don't like football, you may offer this unique Collectible memorabilia as a gift to a friend or keep it, as it will be a time - added value item in your collection..

EVENT INFO
It took place in Qatar from 20 November to 18 December 2022. There were 172 goals scored in 64 matches

Final: Argentina 3 (4) : 3 (2) France  (Argentina won 4-2 on penalty kicks)
Third place: Croatia 2 : 1 Morocco	

BEHIND COLLECTION'S NUMBERS..
Useful info regarding this Special Edition drop:
Editions: 172       (equals to the total number of goals)
DA: 4 - 2  Tz       (special symbolic prices as the score of the final on penalty kicks)
Royalties: 16%      (equals to the number of teams - countries in the round of 16)


CONTROLS

KEYS:

- Spacebar: skip the intro page
- I: switch between game page and the summary (stats) page
- R: Restart
- S: Save a png file


MOUSE:

- Click on intro page to skip (same as the spacebar)
- Click on game page's placeholders to match identical country images - flags (pairs)

----
Made with p5js
